INT. TRI-COUNTY AUCTION BARN - DAY (LATER)

Stitch leans a hand truck against the loading bay and drinks from a paper cup.

STITCH:
That guy I started in on over the net, before they cut me off. You ever hear how it went.

CRICKET:
Don't think so.

Cricket stacks folding chairs against the wall without looking up.

STITCH:
Loaded bags out at the airport. Never flew a day in his life. Taught himself on one of those computer flight things at his kitchen table, years of that.

CRICKET:
Then what happened.

STITCH:
One morning he walks out on the ramp and takes a whole airliner. Empty one. Nobody on it, he just took it and went.

CRICKET:
So he hijacked it.

STITCH:
Wasn't anybody aboard to hijack though. Just him up there on his own.

Cricket sets a chair down and turns around.

STITCH:
Got it up over the mountains and rolled the thing right over, the whole way around. Then they scrambled fighter jets to go box him in.

CRICKET:
What'd he do then.

STITCH:
He just waved at 'em.

Stitch grins down into his cup and drinks.

CUT TO:
